cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM

This paper deals with the problem of manipulating images using natural language descriptions, which is a task that involves computer vision (CV) and natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) and cs.CL (Computation and Language) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper proposes a text-adaptive generative adversarial network (GAN) to generate semantically manipulated images, which involves deep learning techniques such as GANs and neural networks, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) a likely sub-category as well. Additionally, the paper involves image processing and multimedia (MM) techniques, making cs.MM a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper also involves artificial intelligence (AI) techniques such as disentangling visual attributes, making cs.AI a possible sub-category.
